{
  "texts": [
    "Using the Innovations Diffusion Theory, the adoption of AI is due to a combination of factors such as compatibility and complexity (Rogers, 1995).",
    "As AI requires large volumes of training data using sophisticated computational models, its adoption in the publishing industry becomes a challenge given that most publishers in Africa operate on constrained budgets (Molapo, 2020), and lack the human capital needed to develop and implement AI systems.",
    "According to Onoja (2023), AI has the potential to enhance the writing process by providing writers with tools for improved writing, editing, and publishing.",
    "It is apparent from the findings in Onoja's study that AI is being used in the book sector in Africa, in aiding the writing process, although its use is more evident in East and West Africa.",
    "Ngaruiya et al. (2023), in a study of the domestication of AI in Kenya, established that authors have embraced AI-based writing assistant tools for generating content, improving productivity, and meeting client demands."
  ]
}